verbose_text: Finally, human neural progenitor cell (hNPC)-derived neurons were infected with scramble- or TRIM9 specific short hairpin RNA (shRNA) lentivirus for 24 hr, followed by OGD stimulation for 30- or 60-min shRNA mediated knockdown of TRIM9 expression in hNPC derived neurons led to robust IkappaBalpha degradation and increased p65 phosphorylation upon OGD stimulation (XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
